        "content": "<p>I want to prove the following theorem:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Data</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Real</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Basic</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Topology</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">UnitInterval</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">strictMono_of_continuous_injective</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitInterval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitInterval</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hc</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Continuous</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hi</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Function</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Injective</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h_zero</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h_one</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">):</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">StrictMono</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mono_or_anti</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">StrictMono</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">StrictAnti</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Continuous</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">strictMono_of_inj</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hi</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rcases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mono_or_anti</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h_mono</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h_anti</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">assumption</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">exfalso</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">zero_lt_one</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitInterval</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">zero_lt_one'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↑</span><span class=\"n\">unitInterval</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">one_lt_zero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitInterval</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h_zero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">▸</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h_one</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">▸</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h_anti</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">zero_lt_one</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">lt_asymm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">zero_lt_one</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">one_lt_zero</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Continuous.strictMono_of_inj#doc\">docs#Continuous.strictMono_of_inj</a> fails with <code>failed to synthesize\nConditionallyCompleteLinearOrder ↑unitInterval</code>.</p>\n<p>How to prove that <code>unitInterval</code> is an instance of <code>ConditionallyCompleteLinearOrder</code> or <code>CompleteLinearOrder</code>?</p>\n<p>I've tried to use <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=instCompleteLinearOrderElemIccOfFactLe#doc\">docs#instCompleteLinearOrderElemIccOfFactLe</a>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CompleteLinearOrder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitInterval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">instCompleteLinearOrderElemIccOfFactLe</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>but it says <code>failed to synthesize Fact (0 ≤ 1)</code> and I don't know how to provide it with this fact.</p>",
